        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Fredericktown</placeName> [Missouri], <date when="1825-12-06">Dec. 6th 1825</date></p>
<p>My Dear Sir,</p>
<p>My friend <persName>John Mathews</persName>, who will give you this letter, has been an
<persName>inhabitant of this <placeName>Country</placeName></persName> for 26 years; I have been acquainted with <pb n="1238"/>him for 18 years and with much pleasure can recommend him as a
man of integrity and a good citizen. He goes to your <placeName>Country</placeName> with
a view of becoming a citizen thereof. He possesses a knowledge in
<persName>mineralogy</persName>, and wishes to engage in that line. I write this note in
haste as <persName>Mr. Mathews</persName> is on the eve of Departure, would be glad to
give you a full letter&#8212;but can only say, being lately at the <placeName>Mines of
Burton</placeName> your <persName>sister</persName> was well&#8212;My <persName>family </persName>are all well. You will soon
make up your acquaintance with <persName>Mr Mathews</persName>, who will give you all
the local news,</p>

<p><persName>John McArther</persName></p>
<p><persName>Col Stephen F. Austin</persName></p>


        </div1>
